In a press briefing on December 4, 2017, the White House spokesperson addressed several key topics. First, the Supreme Court's decision to allow full enforcement of President Trump's travel ban was discussed. The spokesperson emphasized that the administration is not surprised by the decision and believes the travel ban is necessary for national security. Second, the President spoke with Roy Moore, who is running for Senate in Alabama, and offered his endorsement. The President prefers candidates who support his agenda. Third, it was confirmed that the President has invited Senator Schumer and Speaker Pelosi to the White House. Lastly, the spokesperson addressed the issue of Jerusalem, stating that the President has been clear that it is a matter of when, not if, the US will take action on the city, but no decision on the waiver will be made at this time.